title: EUR/USD:SELL From Resistance ZONE 61.8% FIBO JOLTS News SHORT
name: FOREXN1
contents: The EUR/USD continues its deep retracement and today the price it's inside a strong resistance area ( White rectangle ) between the 50% and the 61.8% Fibo levels. In this area of price, the EUR can be struggling to continue its raising and that can be a good turning area point for the USD. Today there is the JOLTS Job Openings news release it is the Number of job openings during the reported month, excluding the farming industry. Actually, the forecast is under the previous data which means can be a bearish forecast for USD but, the data It's released late, which can impact the market because job openings are a leading indicator of overall employment. Our forecast remains Short for EUR/USD .

title: Long Silver Energy Point
name: Cousin_Fat_Fat
contents:
TVC:SILVER

Silver appears to be putting in a bottom right along the median line and lower parallel of two separate Pitchforks . (Larger Shot of both forks below)

Momentum showing some serious bullish divergence .

Not Shown MACD & RSI - Also showing solid bullish divergence .

Pending a breakout, I would expect that Silver rallies up the arc formation towards the energy point. (Lightning Bolt)

Energy Point = Median Line and/or MLH intersection, this one takes place at approximately $28.50 in late February 2023.

I've set two target areas as potential take profit levels.

T1 = 0.618 Fibonacci Retracement Level = $23.36

T2 = The U-MLH of the purple fork/Energy Point = $27 - $28.50

Let's see what happens.

Fat_Fat

Comment:
Forks + Energy Point

Comment:
(MACD + RSI) Bull Div

for Android","coins":null},{"id":9118689,"parent_id":null,"root_id":9118689,"comment":"Super and logical, thanks for your analysis! Most traders have been predicting long positions already since the recent top, and they continue to try catching the bottom, but every time it fails!  Yes, even in the current market outlook, they continue. Count your losses if you followed their advice!  But in fact, it is absolutely normal because (as everybody knows) 90% lose their capital in the long run and only 10% of the traders/ investors take the huge profits. 

These traders are the ones who have patience instead of FOMO;-)  This is what happens time and time again, and has been for as long as the markets have existed. The psychology of mankind never changes. Huge profits are not for the smaller investors / traders, but for the big firms who play and manipulate the game. That is how it was and how it always will be.

But, the smart traders can profit from what the masses do. All rallies in the current bear market are so-called â€œsucker ralliesâ€ in my opinion. 
A lot of traders forget that just 30 months ago the price of, say, Ethereum was only 86 USD. What rises quickly must come down, and it will. 

In fact, the reason for this crazy bull market of the last 30 months was nothing more than hedge funds and big investors borrowing at zero percent, the printed money from the central banks. The same applies to equity markets.  
And now? Well, with the huge interest rate hikes of 0.75% to bring inflation down to 2%, most of that borrowed money will be pulled out of the markets. It is a chain-reaction. If the markets fall and interest rates rise further, more money will be pulled out of the markets to return to the lenders.  The Dollar will rise quickly because until now the US is the strongest economy at the moment. That is bearish for the markets.

Furthermore, bear markets last longer than one expects and can be very tricky. A new bull market can only start in my opinion when the extremely bearish elements like the war, hyperinflation, the energy crisis are solved or have the outlook it will be solved.
That is not the case yet. It is going to get worse and worse.

What I am writing is my own experience, although I respect others in their view on the markets. 

Let us see what happens at the end of this year en in 2023! Good trading for all!","comment_ast":{"type":"root","children":["Super and logical, thanks for your analysis! title: VET - Analysis
name: MonoCoinSignal
contents:
Over the past week, VET has been expected to rise to the resistance range of $0.0235-$0.024 and reacted negatively after forming a double ceiling pattern in this area. We can still consider the price inside the descending channel . Because the resistance range indicated on the chart was fake broken. But as long as the support range of $0.022 to $0.0225 is maintained, we can expect the price to exit the descending channel .

But if the price hits this resistance area with a negative reaction this time, the price decline can continue to the monthly support area of â€‹â€‹$0.020. For the trend to rise in the 4-hour time frame, breaking this resistance range is necessary to continue the trend. On the RSI indicator, you can consider a narrow ascending channel . As long as the bottom of the channel is maintained, we can expect an upward movement.

title: AXS Axie Infinity The Full Speculative Bubble and Price Target
name: CryptoFundManager
contents:
As you can see in the chart, AXS Axie Infinity made 1375X and went from $0.12 to $165 in only one year.
Now it is trading at $15.08, still high in my opinion!
AXS is an Ethereum based token.

Grayscale expressed concerns over the potential impact on the Ethereum Merge, especially on tokens that run natively on Ethereum:
The Merge may lead to a fork that might have unexpected and unfavorable outcomes and a scenario where stablecoins and tokens locked in smart contracts might not be redeemable.
Token and stablecoin holders might panic and start liquidating their holdings.

In this context, my price target for AXS Axie Infinity is $4.29, still 36X higher from 2 years ago.

Looking forward to read your opinion about it.

Trade active: For comparison, AXS Axie Infinity has about 368,000 active users and a Fully Diluted Market Cap of $4,06 Billion, while RBLX Roblox has 37.1 million daily active users worldwide and a Market Cap of 22.641B.
So RBLX has 100X more users but only 5.4X the Market Cap.
Something isn`t right here!
Either Roblox is undervalued, or AXS Axie Infinity is way overvalued at this level!
Trade active: The sell-off could continue!

title: AUDUSD reached the target, still downtrending
name: ForexKei-Official
contents:
Comment:
AUDUSD reached the target of 0.62519 and is continuously bearish .

Ichimoku Trend Analysis ( KTS ):
- Kumo (Senko span A and B) down
- Kijun sen down
- Tenkan sen down
- Chiko span below candles

Next Scenario:
The market may retrace / consolidate today as it reached the support. However Daily timeframe Kumo is sitll thick, so it could break the support and continuously bearish .

title: ADA: What Can Increase Odds for Another Leg Down Explained
name: WyckoffMode
contents:
Hi Everyone! Notice the Red and Blue Lines in the 2-hour, 4-hour, 6-hour and 8-hour time frames. They are quickly approaching White Level 30. Suggesting we may begin to see another leg down BEGIN on Sunday or Monday. If we are to avoid another leg down, it needs to turn up NOW.

Here is the Near Term Group of time frames (12-hour, 24-hour, 2-Day, 3-Day, 4-Day, 5-Day, 6-Day and Weekly): We also see the Red and Blue Lines approaching White Level 30 as well. However, this will take time to play out in the Near Term Group of time frames. We may potentially be seeing the beginning of another leg down currently in the Short Term Group of time frames.

Here is the Near Term Group:

NOTE the Red and Blue Lines also approaching White Level 30 in the 8-Day, 9-Day, 10-Day, 11-Day and 12-Day time frames: This is why I say, "If we are to avoid another leg down, we need to begin turning up NOW."

Here's the 8-Day, 9-Day, 10-Day, 11-Day and 12-Day time frames:

Comment: UPDATE:

This video posted on October 3, 2022 pointed out WHERE we could go to on another potential leg down.

ADAUSD: We Must Assume We Are Still in Distribution Explained
20:00

Comment: UPDATE:

We get a new 12-hour, 24-hour, 2-Day, 3-Day, 6-Day and Weekly candle in approximately 1 hour 35 minutes from now. We are keeping tabs on the levels of the Red and Blue Lines; with White Level 30 being our focus:
Comment:

Comment: UPDATE:

REMINDER:
The Red Shaded Area would be considered our Preliminary Support Range
for FUTURE Accumulation if we see a Sign of Weakness event in Phase E.
This means we would ANTICIPATE the price action coming up to within proximity of the lower boundary of this Red Shaded Preliminary Support Range.

This means if you are a small swing trader; you would prepare to open a long position AFTER a Sign of Weakness; which you will plan to CLOSE when the price
action is moved up to within PROXIMITY of the Red Shaded Lower Boundary of
FUTURE Preliminary Support Range.

Comment: UPDATE:

We finally came to the point in which "both" Red and Blue Lines fell below white level 30 at the same time; along with the white energy and green line falling. This usually results in a more significant move to the downside.

title: QQQ 08 01 and 22 chart
name: Reallifetrading
contents:
The interesting part here is
the 10/20/50 exponential moving averages on the weekly chart have been SO much more bearish THIS time than the prior 2 crashes. You'll notice a better 'bear' trend with them. We crossed below ALL 3 months ago and they haven't re-crossed since (like they did in 08).

If we currently get an inside week or a retest without a STRONG finish in the next 5 days, this could spell disaster for this market.

I am bearish , I do have puts. I am expecting moves lower.
